README.md
     1тЖТ# Versioning Library for Go
     6тЖТgo-version is a library for parsing versions and version constraints,
     7тЖТand verifying versions against a set of constraints. go-version
     8тЖТcan sort a collection of versions properly, handles prerelease/beta
     9тЖТversions, can increment versions, etc.
    10тЖТ
    11тЖТVersions used with go-version must follow [SemVer](http://semver.org/).
    12тЖТ
    13тЖТ## Installation and Usage
    15тЖТPackage documentation can be found on
    16тЖТ[Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-version).
    17тЖТ
    18тЖТInstallation can be done with a normal `go get`:
    19тЖТ
    20тЖТ```
    21тЖТ$ go get github.com/hashicorp/go-version
    22тЖТ```
    23тЖТ
    24тЖТ#### Version Parsing and Comparison
    26тЖТ```go
    27тЖТv1, err := version.NewVersion("1.2")
    28тЖТv2, err := version.NewVersion("1.5+metadata")
    29тЖТ
    30тЖТ// Comparison example. There is also GreaterThan, Equal, and just
    31тЖТ// a simple Compare that returns an int allowing easy >=, <=, etc.
    32тЖТif v1.LessThan(v2) {
    33тЖТ    fmt.Printf("%s is less than %s", v1, v2)
    34тЖТ}
    35тЖТ```
    36тЖТ
    37тЖТ#### Version Constraints
    39тЖТ```go
    40тЖТv1, err := version.NewVersion("1.2")
    41тЖТ
    42тЖТ// Constraints example.
    43тЖТconstraints, err := version.NewConstraint(">= 1.0, < 1.4")
    44тЖТif constraints.Check(v1) {
    45тЖТ	fmt.Printf("%s satisfies constraints %s", v1, constraints)
    46тЖТ}
    47тЖТ```
    48тЖТ
    49тЖТ#### Version Sorting
    51тЖТ```go
    52тЖТversionsRaw := []string{"1.1", "0.7.1", "1.4-beta", "1.4", "2"}
    53тЖТversions := make([]*version.Version, len(versionsRaw))
    54тЖТfor i, raw := range versionsRaw {
    55тЖТ    v, _ := version.NewVersion(raw)
    56тЖТ    versions[i] = v
    57тЖТ}
    58тЖТ
    59тЖТ// After this, the versions are properly sorted
    60тЖТsort.Sort(version.Collection(versions))
    61тЖТ```
    62тЖТ
    63тЖТ## Issues and Contributing
    65тЖТIf you find an issue with this library, please report an issue. If you'd
    66тЖТlike, we welcome any contributions. Fork this library and submit a pull
    67тЖТrequest.
